ics from grammar, semantics, prosody, literary criticism), and Methods and Tools.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aPragmatics. 4aApplied Linguistics. 4aCommunication. 4aPragmatics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApplied Linguistics, Communication, Pragmatics.1 aAndersen, Gisle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBednarek, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreheny, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBublitz, Wolfram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBublitz, Wolfram, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCap, Piotr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollavin, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConsten, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooke, Maeve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCouper-Kuhlen, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaalder, Saskia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeppermann, Arnulf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomke, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFetzer, Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanks, William F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolly, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuang, Yan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHübler, Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKompa, Nikola, eco